    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 6, then take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Cut your <strong>potato[es]</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized cubes</p><p>Add the <strong>potato cubes</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 25-30 min or until the potatoes are golden and crispy \u2013 these are your <strong>crispy potatoes</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-spanish-style-double-chicken-with-patatas-bravas/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Deseed your <strong>peppers</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut them into thick strips</p><p>Peel and roughly slice your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>pepper strips</strong> and<strong> sliced onion</strong> to a separate baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 20 min or until the veg is soft and tender \u2013 this is your <strong>roasted veg</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-spanish-style-double-chicken-with-patatas-bravas/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the veg is in the oven, boil half a kettle</p><p>Dice your<strong> tomato[es]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Dissolve your <strong>tomato paste</strong> in 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and add your<strong> chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) \u2013 this is your<strong> spicy tomato stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-spanish-style-double-chicken-with-patatas-bravas/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a pot with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced tomato</strong> with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>sugar</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until the tomatoes have broken down</p><p>Add the <strong>spicy tomato stock</strong> to the pan and cook for 3-4 min further or until thickened \u2013 this is your <strong>bravas sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-spanish-style-double-chicken-with-patatas-bravas/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the sauce thickens, cut your<strong> chicken</strong> in half lengthways</p><p>Combine your<strong> ground coriander</strong>, <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong>, 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> on a plate \u2013 this is your <strong>smoky</strong> <strong>spice mix</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> halved chicken</strong> to the <strong>smoky spice mix </strong>and mix until they are fully coated \u2013 this is your <strong>coated chicken</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-spanish-style-double-chicken-with-patatas-bravas/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a separate large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated</strong> <strong>chicken</strong> and cook for 6 min on each side or until the chicken is slightly blackened on the outside and cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>smoky Spanish-style chicken</strong></p><p>(Doubled your protein? Use 2 pans!)</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-spanish-style-double-chicken-with-patatas-bravas/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine your <strong>mayo</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic </strong>(not a big garlic fan? Try using less!),<strong> </strong>1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span><strong> cold water </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> in a small bowl \u2013 this is your <strong>aioli</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-spanish-style-double-chicken-with-patatas-bravas/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>smoky Spanish-style chicken</strong> with the <strong>crispy potatoes</strong> and <strong>roasted veg </strong>to the side</p><p>Top the crispy potatoes with the <strong>bravas sauce</strong> \u2013 these are your <strong>patatas bravas</strong></p><p>Drizzle the<strong> aioli</strong> all over the patatas bravas</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
